UNITED STATES v. LEERBURGER. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 1, 1905.) No. 223 (3,344). Appeal from the Circuit Court of the Upited States for the Southern District of New York. Henry A. Wise Asst. U. S. Atty. William B. Coughtry, for appellee.

Before WALLACE, LACOMBE, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed in open court. For decision- below, see 130 Fed. 1022.
